We denote the SSM core temperature by $T_{c,	ext{SSM}}$ and write the luminosity scalings as
$$L_{pp}\propto S_{11}T_c^{
u_{pp}},\qquad 
L_{CNO}\propto S_{14}T_c^{
u_{CNO}}.$$
In the SSM, we have $L_{pp,	ext{SSM}}=(1-f_{CNO})L_\odot$ and $L_{CNO,	ext{SSM}}=f_{CNO}L_\odot$.
Under the new hypothesis, $S_{14}$ is unchanged, while $S_{11}$ shifts by a factor $(1+\delta_{11})$ and the core temperature $T_c$ adjusts to keep $L_\odot$ fixed. The observed CNO luminosity is $L_{CNO, 	ext{obs}}=(1+\alpha)L_{CNO, 	ext{SSM}}$. Since $L_{CNO} \propto T_c^{
u_{CNO}}$, the temperature must change according to:
$$ rac{L_{CNO, 	ext{obs}}}{L_{CNO, 	ext{SSM}}} = \left( rac{T_c}{T_{c,	ext{SSM}}}ight)^{
u_{CNO}} = 1+\alpha 	ag{1}$$
The total luminosity constraint is $L_{pp} + L_{CNO, 	ext{obs}} = L_\odot$. We can write this in terms of fractional changes from the SSM:
$$ rac{L_{pp}}{L_{pp, 	ext{SSM}}} (1-f_{CNO})L_\odot + (1+\alpha)f_{CNO}L_\odot = L_\odot$$
The change in pp-luminosity is $ rac{L_{pp}}{L_{pp, 	ext{SSM}}} =  rac{S_{11}}{S_{11, 	ext{SSM}}}\left( rac{T_c}{T_{c,	ext{SSM}}}ight)^{
u_{pp}} = (1+\delta_{11})\left( rac{T_c}{T_{c,	ext{SSM}}}ight)^{
u_{pp}}$.
Substituting this into the luminosity constraint and dividing by $L_\odot$:
$$(1-f_{CNO})(1+\delta_{11})\left( rac{T_c}{T_{c,	ext{SSM}}}ight)^{
u_{pp}} + (1+\alpha)f_{CNO} = 1$$
From (1), we have $\left( rac{T_c}{T_{c,	ext{SSM}}}ight)^{
u_{pp}} = \left((1+\alpha)^{1/
u_{CNO}}ight)^{
u_{pp}} = (1+\alpha)^{
u_{pp}/
u_{CNO}}$. For small $\alpha$, this is approximately $1+ rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}\alpha$.
Substituting this into the constraint equation:
$$(1-f_{CNO})(1+\delta_{11})\left(1+ rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}\alphaight) + f_{CNO}(1+\alpha)=1$$
Expanding to first order in the small parameters $\alpha$ and $\delta_{11}$ (dropping the $\mathcal{O}(\alpha\delta_{11})$ term):
$$(1-f_{CNO})\left(1+\delta_{11} +  rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}\alphaight) + f_{CNO} + f_{CNO}\alpha \approx 1$$
$$1-f_{CNO} + \delta_{11}(1-f_{CNO}) +  rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}\alpha(1-f_{CNO}) + f_{CNO} + f_{CNO}\alpha \approx 1$$
$$ \delta_{11}(1-f_{CNO}) +  rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}\alpha -  rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}\alpha f_{CNO} + f_{CNO}\alpha \approx 0$$
Since $f_{CNO}$ is small (~0.01), we can ignore terms multiplied by it except for the leading order terms:
$$\delta_{11}(1-f_{CNO}) \approx - rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}\alpha - f_{CNO}\alpha$$
$$\delta_{11} \approx - rac{\alpha}{1-f_{CNO}}\left( rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}} + f_{CNO}ight) \approx -\alpha\left( rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}} +  rac{f_{CNO}}{1-f_{CNO}}ight)$$
The final result is:
$$\delta_{11} = -\alpha\left( rac{
u_{pp}}{
u_{CNO}}+ rac{f_{CNO}}{1-f_{CNO}}ight)$$
